The Inspector-General of Police, Mohammed Adamu, has approved the posting of new Commissioners of Police to Ogun, Ekiti, Bayelsa and Ondo States, DAILY POST reports. This was contained in a police wireless message obtained by DAILY POST on Tuesday. The police signal tagged, TH.5361/FS/FHQ/ABJ/V.5/689, said CP Edward Awolowo Ajogun is posted to Ogun State; CP Mobayo Babatunde is to report to Ekiti State; CP Abdulakadir Jimoh is deployed to Cross River while CP Okoli C. Michael is to head Bayelsa State command. “The posting is with immediate effect,” the police message read. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-819354 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/IMG-20200721-WA0014.jpg" alt="" width="540" height="960" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/IMG-20200721-WA0014.jpg 540w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/IMG-20200721-WA0014-169x300.jpg 169w" sizes="(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px">